 \sum_{n=0}^\infty x^n=\frac1{1-x}.\tag1 
 \sum_{n=0}^\infty nx^{n-1}=\frac1{(1-x)^2}.\tag2 
 \sum_{n=0}^\infty nx^{n+1}=\frac{x^2}{(1-x)^2}.\tag3 
 \sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{n}{2^{n+1}}=\frac{\left(\frac12\right)^2}{\left(1-\frac12\right)^2}=\large\color{blue}{1}. 
